WEBVTT

00:02.100 --> 00:05.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In the day's other news:
The U.S. military's top
commander said there
will not be any changes

00:05.466 --> 00:08.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
regarding transgender
troops for now.

00:08.500 --> 00:13.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump tweeted
yesterday that he's reinstating
the ban on transgender service

00:13.233 --> 00:15.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
members.

00:15.200 --> 00:19.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, in an internal memo,
Marine General and Joint Chiefs
Chairman Joe Dunford said

00:21.233 --> 00:24.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that pending actual direction
-- quote -- "We will continue
to treat all our personnel with

00:25.166 --> 00:27.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
respect."

00:27.133 --> 00:30.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Army's chief of staff,
General Mark Milley, echoed
that in a Washington appearance.

00:30.566 --> 00:32.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

00:32.666 --> 00:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK MILLEY, U.S. Army Chief
of Staff: We grow up and learn
to obey the chain of command.

00:34.800 --> 00:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And my chain of command is the
secretary of the Army and the
secretary of defense, right,

00:38.633 --> 00:40.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and the president.

00:40.800 --> 00:44.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we will work through the
implementation guidance when
we get it, and then we will

00:46.500 --> 00:48.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
move from there.

00:48.500 --> 00:52.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Defense
Secretary Jim Mattis has been on
vacation, and has made no public

00:52.166 --> 00:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
comment on reinstating the ban.

00:54.700 --> 00:59.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. House of
Representatives has
approved $1.6 billion for
President Trump's proposed

01:00.366 --> 01:01.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wall on the Mexican border.

01:01.966 --> 01:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's the amount he
formally asked for in May.

01:05.133 --> 01:09.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The vote today attached the
money to a much larger bill
that includes a major increase

01:09.533 --> 01:11.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in defense spending.

01:11.000 --> 01:13.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That now goes to the Senate.

01:13.100 --> 01:17.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A top Senate Republican had
sharp words for the president
today over Attorney General

01:17.600 --> 01:19.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Jeff Sessions.

01:19.733 --> 01:23.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Mr. Trump has repeatedly
attacked Sessions for
recusing himself in the
Russia investigation.

01:26.266 --> 01:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Senator Lindsey
Graham, who we have been
hearing about, warned that
there will be -- quote

01:28.233 --> 01:31.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
- - "holy hell" to pay
if Sessions is fired.

01:31.833 --> 01:35.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He also warned against
getting rid of special
counsel Bob Mueller.

01:35.566 --> 01:37.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:37.566 --> 01:39.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: Any effort to go after
Mueller could be the beginning

01:39.566 --> 01:43.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the end of the Trump
presidency, unless Mueller
did something wrong.

01:43.100 --> 01:47.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Right now, I have no
reason to believe that
Mueller is compromised.

01:47.266 --> 01:52.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you got reason to believe
he is compromised and shouldn't
be serving as special counsel,

01:53.166 --> 01:55.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
let me know.

01:55.300 --> 01:58.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Speaker of the
House Paul Ryan also said that
Mueller should stay where he

01:58.333 --> 02:01.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is and continue doing his job.

02:01.100 --> 02:04.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Attorney General Sessions was
traveling in El Salvador today.

02:04.600 --> 02:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said again he will serve
as long as the president wants
him to, but he acknowledged

02:09.033 --> 02:11.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it hasn't been -- quote
-- "the best week."

02:11.766 --> 02:16.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. State Department is
condemning Iran's claim that
it launched an advanced rocket

02:16.033 --> 02:17.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into space.

02:17.733 --> 02:21.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The announcement today
said it happened at a
site east of Tehran.

02:21.400 --> 02:25.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State TV said the rocket
could carry a satellite
weighing about 550 pounds.

02:25.533 --> 02:30.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. says it could lead
to long-range missiles, and
violates the spirit of the Iran

02:31.633 --> 02:33.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nuclear accord.

02:33.633 --> 02:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clashes erupted today between
Palestinians and Israeli
police near a Jerusalem mosque.

02:40.633 --> 02:44.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thousands rushed to pray there
after Israel finished removing
security devices that had

02:45.400 --> 02:47.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
triggered a boycott.

02:47.533 --> 02:51.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Palestinians threw stones and
Israeli police fired back with
tear gas and stun grenades.

02:52.600 --> 02:55.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Red Crescent said
that 37 people were hurt.

02:55.400 --> 02:58.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Each side blamed the
other for the trouble.

02:58.600 --> 03:03.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back in this country,
investigators are asking
why a ride at the Ohio
State Fair broke apart

03:04.733 --> 03:06.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Wednesday evening and
killed a teenager.

03:06.833 --> 03:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Two others were critically hurt.

03:08.933 --> 03:13.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This cell phone video, slowed
down, captured part of the
Fire Ball ride giving way, just

03:15.033 --> 03:17.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
before it hurled
people to the ground.

03:17.500 --> 03:21.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The fair opened as
scheduled today, but all
rides were shut down.

03:21.866 --> 03:24.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Governor John Kasich promised
complete inspections.

03:24.100 --> 03:25.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

03:25.833 --> 03:28.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN KASICH (R), Ohio: I
think about those people
that were hit by debris.

03:28.566 --> 03:33.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think about that moment
when some were thrown
from that carriage.

03:34.966 --> 03:35.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a nightmare.

03:35.966 --> 03:39.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's a terrible situation.

03:39.033 --> 03:44.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But all we can do is what is
humanly possible to make sure
that we provide the safety and

03:45.233 --> 03:47.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the inspections.

03:47.066 --> 03:51.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: State
inspectors had checked the
ride before it began operating.

03:53.233 --> 03:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now officials in several other
states are saying they have
shut down these Fire Ball

03:56.033 --> 03:58.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
rides as well.

03:58.100 --> 04:02.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
