of America apologized
today for President
Trump's speech this week

04:47.200 --> 04:49.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
at the Scouts'
national jamboree.

04:49.733 --> 04:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Michael Surbaugh said,
in an open letter --
quote - - "We sincerely
regret that politics were

04:55.466 --> 04:57.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
inserted into the
scouting program."

04:57.833 --> 05:01.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president appeared
Monday night before
thousands of Scouts,
visitors and staff convened

05:02.666 --> 05:04.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in West Virginia.

05:04.166 --> 05:08.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He laced his speech with a
series of partisan attacks.

